"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to emit","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَفَظَ ٱلنَّفَسَ ٱلْأَخِيرَ / آخِرَ أَنْفَاسِهِ","english":"to emit one's last breath"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spit out","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eject","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to throw out","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speak, enunciate, articulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pronounce, utter, express, say","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"expression, term, word","examples":[{"text":"Ibn Malik\nكَلَامُنَا لَفْظٌ مُفِيدٌ كَٱسْتَقِمْ / وَٱسْمٌ وَفِعْلٌ ثُمَّ حَرْفٌ ٱلْكَلِم\nkalāmunā lafẓun mufīdun kastaqim / wasmun wafiʕlun ṯumma ḥarfun l-kalim","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wording, formulation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"articulation, enunciation, pronunciation"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verb form I from the root ل ف ظ (l f ẓ).\n\nVerbal noun from لَفَظَ (lafaẓa)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37879","headword_ar":"لَفْظٌ","root":"lfZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally an inf. n., (S, Msb,) is used as a subst., (Msb,) signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An expression;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a word;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[more precisely termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZapN","text_ar":"لَفْظَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of words, a phrase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sentence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ak &c.;) [each"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered as such, without regard to its meaning; a word itself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a phrase itself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the latter also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZN murak~abN","text_ar":"لَفْظٌ مُرَكَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compound expression, an expression composed of two"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more words:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Expos. of the Ajroomeeyeh, by the sheykh Khálid; &c.:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malofaZN","text_ar":"مَلْفَظٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alofaAZN","text_ar":"اَلْفَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) dim."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulayofaAZN","text_ar":"اُلَيْفَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Har., p."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"593","text_ar":""},{"kind":"text","text":") and of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAfiZ","text_ar":"مَلَافِظ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZFA wamaEonFY","text_ar":"لَفْظًا وَمَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With respect to the word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"words,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wording, and the meaning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to the actual order of the words; and the order of the sense."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZFA warutobapF","text_ar":"لَفْظًا وَرُتْبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With respect to the actual order of the words, and the order of the proper relative places."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZFA wataqodiyrFA","text_ar":"لَفْظًا وَتَقْدِيرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Literally and virtually."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA waAHida lahu mino","text_ar":"لَا وَاحِدَ لَهُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZihi","text_ar":"لَفْظِهِ"},{"kin